# Pattern promotion

When the same **code shape** keeps appearing (e.g. controller/handler style, service
module, test layout), prefer **promoting it to a project pattern** instead of endless
copy-paste — but **only with owner approval**. Full process:
`docs/specs/agent-workflow.md` §8.

## Observe → propose (do not act unilaterally)

- **Signal, not trigger:** ~3 similar implementations (or one clearly stabilizing shape)
  means **mention it once** to the user — not auto-scaffold, not auto-lint.
- **Ask first:** "This shape is repeating — promote it to a pattern (generator + enforcement)?"
  Do **not** record, scaffold, or add rules without explicit yes.
- **Default: follow-up work.** Unless the user wants promotion **now**, propose a backlog
  item or separate PR — do not derail the current feature session.
- **Propose once per pattern** per session; do not nag on every similar file.

## After owner approval

1. **Record** — section in `docs/architecture.md` for incremental conventions; tiny ADR
   if cross-cutting or hard to reverse (`docs/adr/README.md`).
2. **Extract template** — best example → `tools/<project>/scaffold-<artifact>/templates/`
   with placeholders; reuse `@agent-workflow/generators/lib/*`.
3. **Wire generator** — `pnpm <project>:scaffold-<artifact> --name …` in root `package.json`.
4. **Add enforcement** — ESLint boundaries / import rules and architectural tests first;
   custom ESLint rules only if boundaries are not enough. **Prettier is formatting only**
   — it does not encode architecture.
5. **Point agents at it** — add or extend a `.cursor/rules/*` entry so new artifacts use
   the generator; do not hand-roll.

Portable `@agent-workflow/*` generators stay **doc-only** (ADR-0006). Code scaffolders
live under `tools/<project>/`, not in the toolkit package.
